I had just started my new job and my insurance had not yet kicked in. We knew that we were going to get bum rushed with the cost but his fever was up to 102.8. We went in, put in our names, and were called back quickly - it was Sunday, so there weren't very many people there. The nurse checked him and sent us back into a room. A woman then walked in with a large cart and gave us the pricing structure. We were told that because we were only Category 4, it would cost $1500. But because we were "uninsured" they would reduce that by 55%. So, I gave her my card and she charged me $702. Though we were grossed out by how expensive it was, our son was fine and we had done what we needed to do. Two weeks later, I received a bill from the same hospital for $305 reduced to $138. I called, obviously confused as to why I would be getting a bill for something that I already paid for. Turns out, the $700+ charge was for being in the facility. The $138 was for the physicians bill for giving my son Motrin. Bringing the total to $840 for the trip. Which would have been $1800+ without the "discount"  Now, I have a decent job and am able to pay these bills (humble brag) but it got me thinking.
